If Clojure has a superpower, it's concurrency. Rich Hickey made specific design decisions to make Clojure great at making use of all of the cores on your machine without creating bugs. Clojure concurrency may be awesome, but it's just a bag of tools.

How can you learn to rock your cores?

The answer is not as simple as it seems. You've got a lot of choices in Clojure.
